0have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20This%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2020%20years%20old%20and%20living%20with%20my%20grandmother%20when%20I%20got%20my%20first%20sales%20job%20selling%20printer%20toner%20and%20office%20supplies.%20They%20offered%20me%20%24100%20a%20day%20to%20show%20up%20and%20told%20me%20I%20was%20guaranteed%20to%20last%20three%20weeks.%20After%20three%20weeks%2C%20they%20said%20they%20would%20review%20my%20productivity%20and%20sales%20and%20decide%20whether%20to%20keep%20me%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20between%C2%A0100%20and%20150%20phone%20calls%20a%20day%2C%20and%20I%20was%20on%20the%20phone%20for%20up%20to%20three%20and%20a%20half%20hours.%20It%20was%20very%20difficult%20to%20get%20someone%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsales-consultant-shares-advice-gen-z-overcoming-rejection-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eagree%20to%20purchase%20something%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20phone%20without%20knowing%20you%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20was%20printer%20ink.%20It's%20boring%2C%20and%20people%20don't%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20three-week%20mark%20came%2C%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20did%20pretty%20well.%20We're%20going%20to%20keep%20you%20another%20week.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BSweet.%20Another%20500%20bucks.%20But%2C%20after%20this%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20my%20mindset%20for%20the%20first%20six%20to%20eight%20months.%20Then%2C%20one%20day%2C%20I%20kind%20of%20realized%2C%20%26quot%3BWow.%20I'm%20probably%20not%20going%20anywhere.%20I've%20been%20actually%20doing%20well%2C%20and%20this%20is%20something%20that%20I%20can%20actually%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20six%20years%20of%20sales%20experience%20and%20building%20client%20relationships%2C%20I%20started%20Quire%20Office%20Products%2C%20LLC.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20sold%20over%20%242%20million%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-in-managing-government-contracts-subcontractors-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoner%20and%20office%20supplies.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20that%20I%20learned%20through%20sales%2C%20which%20extends%20to%20everyday%20life%2C%20is%20that%20people%20don't%20remember%20what%20you%20say%2C%20but%20they'll%20always%20remember%20how%20you%20made%20them%20feel.%20This%20is%20my%20advice%20on%20getting%20anyone%20to%20listen%20to%20what%20you%20have%20to%20say%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20you're%20telling%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba6447e3-0923-4a21-96ed-874b48725555%5C%22%3EBe%20genuine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20don't%20like%20to%20be%20sold%20things%20because%20it%20feels%20like%20they're%20being%20tricked%20or%20manipulated%20into%20doing%20something%20that%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20made%20me%20successful%20was%20leaning%20on%20people%20for%20comfort.%20I%20would%20get%20through%20the%20introduction%20part%20and%20ask%20them%20how%20they're%20doing%20and%20they%20would%20respond%20with%20polite%20pleasantries.%20Then%20when%20they%20asked%20me%20about%20myself%2C%20I%20would%20tell%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20a%20new%20job%20and%20it's%20uncomfortable.%20I'm%20sitting%20here%20with%20my%20teddy%20bear%20and%20my%20blanket.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'd%20laugh%2C%20and%20I%20would%20tell%20them%2C%20in%20a%20positive%2C%20fun%20way%2C%20the%20things%20I'm%20doing%20to%20cope%20with%20anxiety.%20I%20think%20it%20made%20them%20more%20comfortable%20because%20it%20made%20me%20more%20relatable%20and%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ec341c6-b295-4a90-9928-43f7ea192db3%5C%22%3EExude%20confidence%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20quickly%20that%20when%20I'm%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20someone%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20hang%20up%20if%20they%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmiling%20when%20you're%20on%20the%20phone%20is%20really%20important.%20People%20can%20actually%20hear%20a%20smile%20through%20the%20phone%20because%20your%20voice%20has%20a%20different%20tone%20that%20people%20can%20identify%20with%20happiness%20and%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20loudly%20also%20makes%20a%20difference%20because%20it%20exudes%20confidence.%20People%20feel%20like%20people%20who%20speak%20loudly%20are%20more%20confident%20because%20people%20who%20are%20shy%20and%20timid%20tend%20to%20mute%20themselves.%20So%20I%20would%20speak%20with%20this%20huge%20amount%20of%20confidence%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20they'd%20have%20confidence%20in%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22641a4df0-788b-489e-9423-6db679db7466%5C%22%3EFind%20a%20connection%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20primary%20focus%20when%20getting%20on%20a%20call%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F8-simple-ways-to-build-strong-relationships-with-your-coworkers-everyday-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emake%20a%20connection%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20build%20a%20relationship.%20One%20way%20that%20I%20would%20do%20that%20is%20by%20breaking%20the%20mold%20of%20the%20traditional%20sales%20call.%20Instead%20of%20introducing%20myself%20to%20the%20office%20manager%20and%20jumping%20into%20what%20kind%20of%20printers%20they're%20running%2C%20I'd%20abandon%20the%20sales%20aspect%20and%20try%20to%20make%20a%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20introduce%20myself%20and%20my%20company%2C%20and%20I%20would%20let%20them%20know%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftreated-job-like-sales-cycle-landed-new-role-two-months-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eit's%20a%20sales%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20them%20to%20feel%20tricked%20or%20manipulated.%20But%20then%20I%20would%20say%20something%20about%20my%20day%20or%20my%20life%20that%20made%20me%20real%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20paint%20them%20a%20vivid%20picture%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20that%20even%20adults%20really%20enjoy%20descriptive%20stories.%20If%20you've%20ever%20listened%20to%20a%20person%20who%20was%20a%20good%20storyteller%2C%20you%20become%20engaged%20with%20what%20they're%20saying%20and%20start%20to%20imagine%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20would%20share%20that%20I%20watched%20a%20game%20the%20night%20before%2C%20and%20they%20ended%20up%20being%20big%20fans%20of%20basketball.%20Then%2C%20I%20would%20ask%20them%20about%20their%20favorite%20players%20or%20what%20school%20they%20went%20to.%20I%20would%20have%2020-%20to%2030-minute%20conversations%20before%20getting%20into%20the%20sales%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20let%20them%20talk%20and%20listen%2C%20and%20I%20would%20give%20them%20feedback.%20Then%2C%20after%20we%20built%20that%20relationship%2C%20I%20would%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20wonderful.%20I%20really%20enjoy%20talking%20to%20you%2C%20but%20I%20did%20call%20you%20for%20a%20reason%2C%20and%20I%20was%20here%20to%20sell%20you%20something.%26quot%3B%20Then%20I%20would%20ask%20about%20what%20kind%20of%20printers%20they%20had%20and%20all%20those%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20customers%2C%20the%20only%20value%20you%20have%20to%20them%20is%20the%20product%20you're%20selling%20and%20the%20price%20you're%20selling%20it%20at.%20The%20only%20thing%20that%20will%20distinguish%20you%20from%20the%20next%20caller%20is%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2-million-sales-lessons-build-relationships-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756720261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b11397a17a8c5b4053b4f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2-million-sales-lessons