lay%20your%20character.%20It%20tells%20the%20interviewer%20that%20you%20are%20polite%2C%20that%20you'd%20likely%20be%20grateful%20to%20receive%20an%20offer%2C%20and%20that%20others%20would%20likely%20enjoy%20working%20alongside%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20a%20thank-you%20will%20show%20you%20are%20resourceful.%20You%20should%20have%20the%20recruiter's%20email%20address%20or%20phone%20number%2C%20and%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20figure%20out%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20make%20an%20educated%20guess%20%E2%80%94%20as%20to%20what%20the%20email%20address%20is%20for%20the%20people%20who%20interviewed%20you.%20Don't%20just%20ask%20the%20recruiter%20for%20their%20email%20addresses%20unless%20your%20emails%20to%20them%20bounce%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20meet%20with%20multiple%20interviewers%20at%20once%2C%20it's%20fine%20to%20thank%20them%20together%20in%20one%20email.%20But%20if%20you%20meet%20with%20them%20individually%2C%20absolutely%20send%20each%20one%20of%20them%20a%20personalized%20thank-you%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ac49a030-85f5-4a9e-bc73-8084a421f0d0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20I%20love%20and%20hate%20to%20see%20in%20a%20thank-you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20love%20is%20when%20a%20candidate%20shares%20something%20they%20learned%20in%20the%20interview%20that%20makes%20them%20excited%20about%20the%20job%20or%20the%20company.%20This%20should%20be%20new.%20Don't%20just%20pull%20from%20the%20job%20description.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20is%20to%20thank%20the%20interviewers%20for%20their%20time%20and%20for%20considering%20you.%20This%20seems%20obvious%2C%20but%20not%20everyone%20does%20it%20right%20because%20they%20don't%20actually%20say%20it.%20They%20just%20say%20that%20they're%20following%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20is%20to%20remind%20whoever%20you%20met%20with%20how%20you%20can%20solve%20a%20problem%20or%20meet%20a%20need%20that%20was%20raised%20in%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20hate%20to%20see%20the%20most%20in%20a%20thank-you%20is%20when%20the%20candidate%20gets%20the%20interviewer's%20name%20wrong.%20I%20cannot%20tell%20you%20how%20many%20thank-yous%20I%20have%20received%20that%20say%2C%20Dear%20Lauren.%20Lauren%20is%20not%20my%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20turnoff%20is%20when%20the%20thank-you%20is%20just%20a%20retelling%20of%20the%20candidate's%20skills.%20I%20don't%20need%20a%20new%20cover%20letter%20from%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20thing%20I%20don't%20like%20to%20see%20is%20when%20it's%20all%20about%20the%20candidate%20%E2%80%94%20the%20thank-you%20is%20used%20as%20another%20selling%20tool%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20really%20not%20about%20being%20thankful.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20come%20across%20as%20arrogant%20or%20slimy%20by%20saying%20something%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BThanks%20for%20meeting%20with%20me.%20Here%20are%2010%20reasons%20why%20you%20should%20hire%20me.%20Have%20a%20good%20day.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20you%20want%20to%20personalize%20the%20message.%20For%20example%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20liked%20hearing%20in%20the%20interview%20about%20%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e355d524-206f-4da7-9853-fbf6a25c3b5f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmail%2C%20text%2C%20or%20old-school%20mail%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20use%20email%2C%20which%20makes%20sense%20because%20hiring%20decisions%20are%20often%20made%20within%2024%20to%2048%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20mind%20a%20text.%20I'd%20rather%20hear%20from%20you%20than%20not%20hear%20from%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20exception%20is%20if%20the%20interviewer%20says%20they%20have%20a%20long%20turnaround%20time%20to%20make%20a%20decision.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20you%20might%20send%20a%20handwritten%20thank-you%20note%20in%20the%20real%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20go%20old%20school%2C%20you're%20really%20going%20to%20be%20memorable.%20You%20should%20also%20still%20send%20a%20thank-you%20by%20email%2C%20though%2C%20in%20case%20your%20letter%20gets%20lost%20in%20the%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sincere%20and%20keep%20it%20brief.%20I've%20seen%20thank-you%20notes%20that%20I%20thought%20were%20very%20nice%20and%20genuine%2C%20and%20they%20were%20maybe%20four%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20going%20to%20say%20a%20thank-you%20note%20will%20get%20you%20the%20job.%20But%20when%20it's%20a%20tough%20hiring%20decision%20and%20one%20candidate%20sends%20a%20thank-you%20note%20and%20the%20other%20doesn't%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20the%20one%20who%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225dc59329-7c94-4a1d-9595-45c3e42b033a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuture%20benefits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20I've%20learned%20in%20my%20career%20is%20how%20small%20industries%20are.%20Even%20if%20you%20don't%20end%20up%20working%20for%20the%20company%20at%20this%20time%2C%20in%20this%20role%2C%20you%20never%20know%20what%20the%20future%20holds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20the%20hiring%20manager%20knows%20of%20a%20different%20role%20within%20the%20organization.%20It%20would%20be%20very%20easy%20for%20that%20person%20to%20forward%20your%20thank-you%20email%20to%20their%20colleague%2C%20along%20with%20a%20quick%20message%20that%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BJoe%20Smith%20wasn't%20a%20fit%20for%20my%20role%2C%20perhaps%20he'd%20be%20for%20yours%3F%26quot%3B%20You've%20already%20started%20off%20positively%20with%20your%20potential%20new%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20perhaps%20you'll%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20at%20the%20same%20company%20in%20the%20future.%20If%20the%20recruiter%20takes%20notes%20like%20I%20do%2C%20your%20thank-you%20will%20be%20in%20your%20candidate%20profile%2C%20and%20that%20will%20set%20you%20apart%20for%20the%20new%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20possible%20that%20a%20few%20years%20from%20now%2C%20the%20hiring%20manager%20you%20thanked%20is%20at%20a%20new%20company%2C%20and%20you%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20there.%20You%20already%20have%20some%20goodwill%20built%20up%20because%20you're%20one%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20to%20have%20ever%20sent%20that%20manager%20a%20thank-you%20in%20his%20or%20her%20entire%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-to-follow-up-after-job-interview-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756719781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a7416f194a2d49b8aeedfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-to-follow-up-after-job-interview-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Writing%20a%20thank-you%20letter%20can%20help%20you%20stand%20out%20from%20the%20competition%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20you%20do%20it%20right.%20Here's%20how.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sneedleman%40businessinsider.com%20(Sarah%20E.%20Needleman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-to-follow-up-after-job-interview-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Ranks%20Highest%20In%20Asia's%20Best%20Workplaces%20List%20With%2048%20Companies%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22India%20ranks%20highest%20in%20great%20places%20to%20work%20in%20Asia%2C%20with%2048%20out%20of%20the%20top%20100%20organisations%20operating%20in%20India%2C%20a%20report%20said%20on%20Monday.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756719676000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-09%2F84icb8og_india-ranks-highest-in-great-places-to-work-in-asia_625x300_01_September_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-ranks-highest-in-asias-best-workplaces-list-with-48-companies-according-to-a-report-by-great-place-to-work-9195990%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20ranks%20highest%20in%20great%20places%20to%20work%20in%20Asia%2C%20with%2048%20out%20of%20the%20top%20100%20organisations%20operating%20in%20India%2