omy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20cofounder%20tells%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlison%20Bennett%2C%20a%20mom%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20has%20been%20going%20%26quot%3Bfull%20'90s%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20efforts%20to%20avoid%20buying%20her%208-year-old%20a%20phone.%20Bennett%20bought%20her%20an%20MP3%20player%20for%20music%2C%20rents%20DVDs%20for%20movies%2C%20and%20gets%20paper%20delivery%20of%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she's%20found%20another%20way%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmonitor-teen-cellphone-safety-parenting-experts-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eput%20off%20getting%20her%20daughter%20a%20cellphone%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20She%20ordered%20three%20%2475%20Tin%20Can%20%26quot%3Blandline%26quot%3B%20phones%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20her%208-year-old%20daughter%2C%20and%20two%20for%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20my%20daughter%20to%20be%20able%20to%20chat%20with%20her%20friends%2C%20like%20I%20did%20as%20a%20child%20in%20the%20'90s%26quot%3B%20Bennett%20said%20%E2%80%94%20without%20worrying%20about%20all%20the%20other%20stuff%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20mobile%20phone.%20She%20said%20she%20heard%20about%20the%20Tin%20Can%20on%20a%20Facebook%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETin%20Can%20is%20a%20phone%20that%20runs%20off%20your%20home's%20WiFi.%20It's%20similar%20to%20a%20regular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-voip%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVoIP%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20except%20that%20it%20has%20parental%20controls%20so%20that%20only%20approved%20contacts%20can%20call%2C%20and%20only%20during%20approved%20hours.%20There's%20also%20a%20free%20plan%20where%20Tin%20Can%20users%20can%20call%20only%20other%20Tin%20Can%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20was%20founded%20last%20fall%20by%20three%20friends%20in%20the%20Seattle%20area.%20Two%20of%20them%20were%20dads%2C%20and%20they%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20phone%20for%20their%20own%20kids.%20They%20sat%20around%20the%20kitchen%20table%20with%20soldering%20irons%2C%20working%20on%20a%20prototype%20with%20an%20old%20corded%20landline%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20know%20if%20this%20would%20be%20a%20business%20or%20a%20cool%20walkie-talkie%2C%26quot%3B%20Chet%20Kittleson%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Tin%20Can%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20they%20started%20giving%20a%20few%20of%20these%20phones%20to%20their%20kids'%20friends%20so%20they%20would%20have%20someone%20to%20talk%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Let's%20just%20see%20if%20our%20kids%20use%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kittleson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20lost%20their%20minds.%20Kids%20used%20the%20crap%20out%20of%20the%20thing.%20They%20were%20so%20excited%20when%20it%20rang%2C%20they%20would%20jump%20over%20the%20couch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20raised%20%243.5%20million%20so%20far%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20including%20from%20Pioneer%20Square%20Ventures%2C%20Newfund%20Capital%2C%20Mother%20Ventures%2C%20and%20Solid%20Foundation%2C%20among%20a%20few%20others.%20The%20are%20seven%20full-time%20employees%2C%20including%20Kittleson%20and%20his%20co-founders%2C%20Max%20Blumen%20and%20Graeme%20Davies.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%2211400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tin%20Can%20phone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b1d9d3a17a8c5b4053c0a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%227600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Tin%20Can%20phone%20lets%20kids%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20in%20a%20closed%20network.%3Cp%3ETin%20Can%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKittleson%20said%20they've%20sold%20%26quot%3Btens%20of%20thousands%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20phones%20since%20launching%20in%20early%202025%20%E2%80%94%20and%20tens%20of%20thousands%20just%20in%20the%20last%20month.%20They're%20backordered%20until%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Tin%20Can%20comes%20as%20a%20newish%20movement%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felementary-aged-child-wants-cellphone-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparents%20are%20wanting%20to%20delay%20giving%20older%20kids%20and%20tweens%20a%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20as%20late%20as%20possible%20%E2%80%94%20some%20not%20until%20high%20school%2C%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20leaves%20kids%20stuck%20without%20a%20way%20to%20communicate%20with%20friends%2C%20and%20forces%20parents%20to%20act%20as%20their%20kids'%20social%20secretary%2C%20fielding%20texts%20from%20other%20parents%20to%20set%20up%20playdates%20or%20other%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20market%20for%20older%20kids%20who%20aren't%20quite%20ready%20for%20a%20full%20cellphone%2C%20but%20need%20to%20communicate%20with%20parents%20or%20friends.%20This%20market%20is%20mainly%20served%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20smartwatches%2C%20flip%20phones%2C%20or%20devices%20from%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgabb-smartphone-review-teens-kids-social-media-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGabb%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Troomi%2C%20or%20Pinwheel%20that%20are%20usually%20Android%20smartphones%20with%20heavy%20parental%20control%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20WiFi%20%26quot%3Blandline%26quot%3B%20phone%20is%20something%20different%20than%20just%20a%20safe%20cellphone%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20parents%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ffamily%2Farchive%2F2025%2F06%2Flandline-kids-smartphone-alternative%2F683203%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erediscovering%20%3C%2Fa%3Eit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20added%20benefit%20is%20giving%20kids%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20phone%20etiquette.%20(Alarmingly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-phone-ansewring-hello-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esome%20Gen%20Zers%20don't%20say%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20an